node.text: “If you can only be tall, because somebody’s on their knees, then you have a serious problem.” PLEASE start your Sunday watching this incredible clip with Toni Morrison. Charlie Rose (ugh) initially asks Morrison if she still encounters racism, despite her success. She turns the question around, explaining how racism is the only tool white supremacists have to undermine Black people’s success. It’s a timely and powerful clip with useful framing for understanding and confronting white supremacist terror in 2021.

node.title: Toni Morrison On Race And Racism

-Why there’s so much time between the election and inauguration?!? (It has to do with horses and buggies) ⁣
Find the Betches Sup podcast on Spotify, or on iTunes via betches.co/suppod (we’ll have a swipe up in Stories)⁣

node.text: Where’s the line between celebrating femininity and falling into sexist tropes? Last month, Sup hosts sat down to discuss the question on all of our minds: is it sexist to stan Kamala Harris’s outfits? What do we signal to some women when we only celebrate others? Do we apply the same standard to women whose views we don’t agree with? It was a fascinating and cathartic conversation. Listen to the full episode at the link in bio/Stories betches.co/sexism

node.title: Is It Sexist To Stan Kamala Harris’s Outfits?

node.text:
Good morning to MacKenzie Scott and MacKenzie Scott only. (@rohita.kadambi)

Last year while her ex was planning a joyride for the wealthy, MacKenzie Scott set a record for most charitable donations given in a single year -- $5.8 billion. She’s donated $2.7 billion already this year, mainly to groups that promote racial equality, the arts, and COVID recovery and relief. She is such a prolific giver -- often reaching out personally to organizations to help -- that others have tried to imitate her. Earlier this year, she got married a science teacher. Winning.

Tom Brady’s political past is sus, but the former guy definitely *hates* this. 

Trump is famously a huge Tom Brady fan, having enthusiastically defended Brady during the deflategate situation -- seeing himself in a fellow “winner” who he thought people were falsely rallying against. Brady said Trump called him often after games and the two went golfing together. Brady was spotted with a MAGA hat in his locker in 2015, but declined to say who he supported in 2016 and skipped a 2017 White House meeting with Trump. Trump was reportedly furious. 🎥 @cspan

node.text:
Any bed can be an anti-sex bed if you try hard enough. Amid some excited chatter that the cardboard beds created for Olympians and Paralympians may be designed to interfere with intimacy, turns out the beds can withstand up to 440 pounds and plenty of movement, as Irish gymnast Rhys McClenaghan demonstrated. The recylable frames are made by Japanese company Airweave, which says they’re stronger than steel. 

Olympic hookups pose threat of disease spread at every games, but concerns are obviously higher during a global pandemic. Athletes will still be provided condoms -- just at the end of the games. Hugs and handshakes are also discouraged.
